---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Home"
  description="Farlink Systems handles industrial automation, electrical testing, arc flash studies, and field support for industrial, commercial, water, and government facilities."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <span class="eyebrow">Industrial automation and electrical work</span>
        <h1>Controls, testing, and studies for sites that have to stay running.</h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">
          Farlink Systems handles PLC and HMI work, electrical testing, arc flash studies, and field support. We build around
          the process, the equipment, and the people who have to operate it.
        </p>

        <ul class="pill-list hero-pills">
          <li>PLC and HMI work</li>
          <li>Electrical testing</li>
          <li>Arc flash studies</li>
          <li>Water and government sites</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="button-row">
          <a href="/services" class="btn">See services</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--ghost">Talk about a project</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="surface hero-panel">
        <span class="eyebrow">What we handle</span>
        <ul class="list-reset checklist">
          <li>Controls design, PLC programming, HMI screens, and startup support.</li>
          <li>Acceptance testing, commissioning, troubleshooting, and power quality work.</li>
          <li>Arc flash, short circuit, and coordination studies with clear deliverables.</li>
          <li>Industrial, commercial, water, and government work.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="hero-panel-note">
          <span class="kicker">Based in Fort Mill, South Carolina</span>
          <p>We keep the site simple for the same reason we keep project scope clear: less noise, better work.</p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--tight">
    <div class="container intro-grid">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">How we work</span>
        <h2>Clear scope. Straight answers. Work that holds up in the field.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="stack">
        <p>
          We start with the process, the existing conditions, and the operating constraints. Then we build the controls,
          testing plan, or study around that.
        </p>
        <p>
          No padded language. No vague deliverables. Just solid engineering, clean documentation, and follow-through when the
          system has to start up and run.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--muted">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="eyebrow">Core services</span>
        <h2>Most projects land in one of these four buckets.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="info-grid info-grid--2 services-grid">
        <article class="card info-card service-card">
          <span class="kicker">01</span>
          <h3>Industrial automation</h3>
          <p>PLC programming, HMI work, controls design, integration, commissioning, and support after startup.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card info-card service-card">
          <span class="kicker">02</span>
          <h3>Electrical testing</h3>
          <p>Acceptance testing, relay testing, commissioning, troubleshooting, and power quality work.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card info-card service-card">
          <span class="kicker">03</span>
          <h3>Arc flash and power studies</h3>
          <p>Arc flash, short circuit, and coordination studies with practical outputs that people can use.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card info-card service-card">
          <span class="kicker">04</span>
          <h3>Water and government work</h3>
          <p>Engineering support for public infrastructure and federal projects where documentation and compliance matter.</p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="button-row">
        <a href="/services" class="btn btn--ghost">Full service list</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container info-grid info-grid--3">
      <article class="card info-card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Process first</span>
        <p>We do not start with a canned package. We start with what the site needs to do.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card info-card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Field aware</span>
        <p>Design choices have to survive startup, maintenance, and real operators on a real schedule.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card info-card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Plain language</span>
        <p>You should know what is being done, what it costs, and what you are getting back.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section cta-section">
    <div class="container cta-box surface">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Need help on a project?</span>
        <h2>Send the scope. If you have drawings, send those too.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-actions">
        <p>Email is the fastest path. We can sort out whether you need controls work, testing, a study, or some mix of all three.</p>
        <div class="button-row">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact Farlink</a>
          <a href="mailto:david@farlinksystems.com" class="btn btn--ghost">Email David</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 3rem 0 2.5rem;
  }

  .hero-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .hero-copy h1 {
    max-width: 13ch;
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
  }

  .hero-lead {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    max-width: 58ch;
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
  }

  .hero-pills {
    margin-top: 1.35rem;
    max-width: 48rem;
  }

  .hero-panel {
    padding: 1.4rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-panel-note {
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .hero-panel-note p {
    margin-top: 0.55rem;
  }

  .intro-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .services-grid {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .service-card {
    min-height: 100%;
  }

  .cta-section {
    padding-top: 2rem;
  }

  .cta-box {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .cta-box h2 {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    max-width: 14ch;
  }

  .cta-actions p {
    max-width: 48ch;
  }

  @media (min-width: 860px) {
    .hero-grid {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.45fr) minmax(320px, 0.95fr);
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .intro-grid {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .cta-box {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, 0.9fr);
      align-items: end;
    }
  }
</style>
